  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, because they wasn't allowed-- neither Christian nor Jewish religion-- to be taught.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So there's no young people really learn neither.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "All these buildings was open only like museums.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You could go in.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "If you want to pray, pray.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "If not, not.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But it was no service.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "And the synagogue where in this outskirts of Budapest where my parents lived-- you know, my family lived-- I went back there on the very beginning.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And I went to that synagogue.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And I saw about-- they had 10 people at the most who-- who was there, and everybody asked one another, did you heard of my this name and that name, and nobody-- nobody.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And it was very painful, because I remember occasionally on high holy days, my grandmother was taking me to-- my mother didn't-- my grandmother taking me to the synagogue.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And it was jam packed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "You know-- women upstairs.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Men downstairs.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I mean, there was nobody.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And everybody saw-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] destroyed mentally, really, because as we recovered slowly, you know, but mentally it's very hard to come to terms with what happened.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It's impossible.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yeah.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Yes, somebody was lives there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I heard later on from people what happened when we left-- it-- all valuables was taken by the government or whoever.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I don't know.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But then, in places we left open, what nobody find it with the key, and then the general public just can go and have their selves, you know, like saucepans and plates and, you know, whatever didn't find it valuable, the government, of the time.",
      "word_count": 45
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But then-- but then a remark I heard-- there is no home in Hungary, which haven't got some property from a Jewish home.",
      "word_count": 23
    }
  ],
